Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.49,0:35:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这样太空服就很容易撕破或开裂{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So you could easily get a tear or a rip in the space suit,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.66,0:35:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而那将会是灾难性的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that would be catastrophic.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.04,0:35:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽管危机重重 宇航员还是驾着小型漫游车{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Despite the dangers, the astronaut takes the small rover,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.20,0:35:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}载着额外的氧气补给 冲入沙尘暴{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}loaded with extra oxygen, out into the storm.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.05,0:35:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她一个一个地把队友接回返地舱{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And one by one, she brings her crew mates back to the Earth Return Vehicle.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.10,0:35:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是就在即将到达安全地点时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But just a few feet from safety...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.91,0:35:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}粗糙的沙尘就撕破了指挥官的太空服{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The abrasive dust tears a section of the commander's suit,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.58,0:35:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将他暴露在几近真空的火星大气层下{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}exposing him to the near-vacuum of the martian atmosphere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.08,0:35:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你的太空服有一个漏洞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If... If your space suit springs a leak,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.90,0:35:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者它突然降压 完全打开了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or if it's a violent decompression, where your suit is ripped open,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.87,0:35:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你只能保持几秒清醒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you might not have more than a few seconds to remain conscious{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.14,0:35:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来面对将会发生的事{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and see what's going to happen to you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.02,0:35:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你情况不妙{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You would be in a very bad way.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.36,0:36:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好似在地球上深度潜水后上浮{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You would be not dissimilar to coming up from a very deep dive on the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.52,0:36:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这将是一次非常痛苦的经历{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It would be a very painful experience.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.48,0:36:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你有减压问题{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If you have a decompression problem{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.89,0:36:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这将是很严重且致命的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it can get very serious and lethal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.21,0:36:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你将面临可怕而迅速的死亡{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You would die a horrible death and very quickly as well.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.38,0:36:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}除非他的同伴能马上采取措施{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Unless his crew mates can do something immediately,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.00,0:36:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}否则他将会成为火星上的第一具人类尸体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the commander will be the first human corpse on Mars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.78,0:36:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在我们对不远未来的设想中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In our scenario of the near future,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.13,0:36:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}首批登陆火星的探索者{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the first explorers on Mars{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.90,0:36:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}同时经受住了近乎致命的撞击{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}have survived a near fatal crash{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.23,0:36:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与在这充满敌意的星球上的危险旅程{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and a dangerous trek across a hostile planet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.76,0:36:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但如今 一场磨蚀性砂尘形成的风暴{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But now, a storm of abrasive dust{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.77,0:36:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在任务指挥官的太空服上撕开了一个洞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}has torn a hole in mission commander's spacesuit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.72,0:36:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是宇航员最为害怕的情况{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's the one thing the astronauts fear above everything else.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.68,0:36:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}失去意识前 你只有10到12秒的时间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You've got 10 or 12 seconds before you lose consciousness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.66,0:37:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种情况下最好立即呼气 排空肺部{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You better exhale, right away. Empty your lungs,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.57,0:37:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不然的话它们便会迅速扩张乃至爆裂{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because otherwise they'll quickly expand and rupture.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.97,0:37:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太空服破损十二秒后 指挥官已不省人事{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Twelve seconds after his suit tore, the commander is unconscious.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.94,0:37:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的皮肤开始发青{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}His skin is turning blue.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.49,0:37:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的组员只有不到九十秒的时间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}His crewmates have less than 90 seconds{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.74,0:37:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将他送进返地舱的气闸室{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to get him through the ERV's airlock{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.52,0:37:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}进行紧急输氧 否则他的血液循环将停止{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and administer emergency oxygen before his blood circulation ceases{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.95,0:37:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的器官将永久地停止工作{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and his organs shut down forever.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.68,0:37:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在失去意识之后{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}After you've lost consciousness,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.79,0:37:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最好有人能在接下来的一分半钟内{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you hope that someone will hook you up to pressurized oxygen{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.13,0:37:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为你提供压缩氧气{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}within the next minute and a half.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.28,0:37:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果得不到的话 你必死无疑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If you don't get hooked up, you'll die for sure.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.71,0:37:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}若能得到救助 并能再次呼吸氧气{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If you do get hooked up, and you start breathing oxygen again,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.29,0:37:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}等你挺过来 一般来说{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it turns out that, when you come to,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.32,0:37:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不会造成太多的永久性伤害{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there's usually not much permanent damage.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.10,0:37:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}指挥官在千钧一发之际得以幸存{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The commander survives with seconds to spare.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.93,0:38:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽管他受伤了 他还是能够痊愈{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Despite his injuries, he will make a full recovery.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.74,0:38:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很快 队员们恢复了精力{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Soon, the crew is back to full strength,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.51,0:38:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并开始进行各种实验活动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}working and performing experiments.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.76,0:38:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}火星探索已正式展开{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The exploration of Mars has begun in earnest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.48,0:38:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对我来说火星将会挑战一切{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Mars to me would challenge{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.91,0:38:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类历史上有过的探索经验{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}all the expedition experiences that we've had throughout our history.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.16,0:38:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}过往积累的宝贵经验均会尽数应用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It will take all the best lessons learned from all past expeditions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.24,0:38:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比如极地经验 丛林经验{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The polar ones, the ones through the jungles,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.10,0:38:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及北美大陆经验{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the ones through North America.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.16,0:38:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}火星是个极具挑战性的地方 它极度无情{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Mars is a super-challenging place; it's very unforgiving.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.48,0:38:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在地球上 即便遇上麻烦{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Here on Earth, if things go wrong,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.25,0:38:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们仍有空气可呼吸 仍有水源可饮用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we can rely on there being air to breathe and water to drink.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.25,0:38:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但在火星上 如果出了问题{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}On Mars, if something goes wrong,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.76,0:38:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那么情况马上会变得更加糟糕{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}then the situation is automatically much more serious.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.16,0:39:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是宇航员已证明他们能适应火星上的环境{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But the astronauts have proven that they can adapt to the martian environment.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.92,0:39:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和极地探索者一样 他们抵御着刺骨低温{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Like polar explorers, they protect themselves from the frigid temperatures.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.54,0:39:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像沙漠探索者一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Like desert explorers,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.90,0:39:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们学会与无处不在的砂尘共同生活{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they learn to live with the ever-present dust.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.87,0:39:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在我们火星协会运作的沙漠研究站里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In our own desert station that the Mars Society runs{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.98,0:39:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们带去一台高端显微镜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we brought a really superb microscope,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.24,0:39:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是运抵之后数周之内 它就被砂尘弄坏了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but it was disabled by dust within a few weeks of it's arrival.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.78,0:39:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而另一方面 一些工艺更为粗糙的显微镜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}On the other hand, some much cruder kind of microscopes,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.80,0:39:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}类似于一般本科学生用的一类{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}similar to the kind that college students use routinely,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.69,0:39:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}经证实相当强韧{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}have proved very robust.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.98,0:39:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在前线环境中 你想要的不会是匹赛马{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In a frontier environment, you don't want to bring a racehorse.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.81,0:39:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你想要的会是匹骡子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You want to bring a mule.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.26,0:39:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然而火星上也不见得处处都比地球艰难{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Not everything on Mars is more difficult than on Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.82,0:39:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}例如地表风就十分柔和 根本无法对{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The surface winds, for instance, are mild, too weak to threaten{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.16,0:39:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇航员或是他们的器械造成威胁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the astronauts or their instruments.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.94,0:40:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}火星大气层的厚度只有地球大气的百分之一{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The martian atmosphere is only 1% as thick as Earth's atmosphere,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.57,0:40:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以说如果你站在地上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and so if you're on the ground{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.82,0:40:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对面96公里每小时的风刮过来时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and a 60 mile an hour wind kicked up,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.12,0:40:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你只会有10公里每小时的风轻拂的感觉{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you would only feel the force of a 6 mile an hour wind.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.23,0:40:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们这有个风速计 或是叫测风速计{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We have here an anemometer, or wind-gage{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.36,0:40:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用来测量当前风速{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which helps us measure the wind speed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.99,0:40:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的设计实际上很简单{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's a very simple design really.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.55,0:40:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上面的这些风杯在风刮过的时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You've got these cups on top that capture the wind{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.25,0:40:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}捕捉风力从而使得风杯旋转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as it blows by and causes the cups to spin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.71,0:40:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你只用记下风杯的旋转次数{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You simply count the number of rotations of the cups,{\r}
